A yearly subscription is refundable within 14 days of purchase and includes a 365-day membership. The government struck a deal with Total in 1967 to allow Natref to avoid oil-transportation costs as an incentive to build the plant at an inland location, Transnet said. While the facility south of Johannesburg had been paying the related tariffs, Total and Sasol subsequently sought discounts through court claims. “Transnet is of the view that if these tariffs cannot be recovered from Natref, they will have to be recovered from customers, resulting in all tariffs other than crude tariffs increasing by at least 10%,” Transnet said. Sasol wasn’t immediately available to respond to an email seeking comment. © 2021 Bloomberg